<section sectnbr = "1D">
<servcat sctnbr = "01" scnbr = "04">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENCP70A1406024" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "1">
<title>
Timing Chain and Chain Tensioner Removal and Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENCP70A1406023">Timing Chain and Chain Tensioner Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A1406024001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
After timing chain is removed, never turn crankshaft and camshafts independently more than specified range (“a” and “b”) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If either of those shafts is turned over the specified range, interference may occur between piston and valves and valves themselves, and parts related to piston and valves may be damaged.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A141061.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "84.789mm" ver = "01" gw = "142" gh = "224"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.229in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.536in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.324in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.280in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Timing mark on VVT actuator
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
4.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Notch on cylinder block
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Notch on cylinder head
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
“a”: 
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
90&#176;
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
3.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Key
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
“b”:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
15&#176;
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
If it is necessary to rotate the camshaft after removing timing chain, turn crankshaft counterclockwise and position the key (1) within an angle of 30&#176; to 90&#176; from TDC as shown in the figure below before rotating the camshaft in order to prevent the valves from coming in contact with the pistons.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A141058.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "37.283mm" ver = "01" gw = "129" gh = "89"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "0.588in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "0.560in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
“a”:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
30&#176;
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
“b”:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
90&#176;
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove timing chain cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1406018"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
By turning crankshaft, align camshafts and crankshaft at specific position as follows.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Align timing marks (1) on intake VVT actuator with surface of cylinder head (2).
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Align timing marks (1) on exhaust VVT actuator with notch (3) on cylinder head.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Position crankshaft sprocket key (4) with notch (3) on cylinder block.
</ptxt>
</s2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove timing chain tensioner adjuster (5).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove timing chain tensioner (6).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove timing chain guide (7).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove timing chain (8) and crankshaft timing sprocket (9).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A141062.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "104.587mm" ver = "01" gw = "145" gh = "280"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A1406024002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENCP70A1406025">Timing Chain and Chain Tensioner Inspection</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Align timing mark (1) on intake VVT actuator with surface of cylinder head (2).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Align timing mark (1) on exhaust VVT actuator with notch (3) on cylinder head.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set key (4) and turn crankshaft to match key with notch (3) on cylinder block.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A141063.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "110.162mm" ver = "01" gw = "142" gh = "296"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install crankshaft timing sprocket to crankshaft.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install timing chain while aligning painted plates (1) with timing marks (2) on intake and exhaust VVT actuators.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install timing chain while aligning painted plate (3) with timing mark (4) on crankshaft timing sprocket.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A141066.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "91.451mm" ver = "01" gw = "139" gh = "243"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Apply engine oil to sliding surface of timing chain guide (1) and install it as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Tighten guide bolts to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T1D016">
<t-part>
Timing chain guide bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
11
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
1.1
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
8.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Apply engine oil to sliding surface of chain tensioner (2) and install chain tensioner and spacer.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Tighten tensioner bolt to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T1D017">
<t-part>
Timing chain tensioner bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
b
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
25
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.5
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
18.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A141064.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "58.703mm" ver = "01" gw = "172" gh = "150"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Check that timing mark (2) on intake and exhaust camshaft VVT actuators are in match with painted plates (1) of timing chain and timing mark (4) on crankshaft timing sprocket is in match with painted plate (3) of timing chain.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A141066.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "91.451mm" ver = "01" gw = "139" gh = "243"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Screw in plunger (1) by turning body (2) in arrow direction and install a retainer (3) (1.4 mm (0.055 in.) diameter wire or the like) to hold plunger in place.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH0B140065.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "44.396mm" ver = "01" gw = "180" gh = "109"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install timing chain tensioner adjuster (1) with the retainer (2).
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Tighten timing chain tensioner adjuster bolts to specified torque, and then remove the retainer from chain tensioner adjuster.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T1D018">
<t-part>
Timing chain tensioner adjuster bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
11
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
1.1
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
8.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A141064.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.513mm" ver = "01" gw = "156" gh = "104"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Apply engine oil to timing chain, and then turn crankshaft clockwise 720&#176;, and confirm that the following conditions are satisfied:
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Timing mark (1) on intake VVT actuator is aligned with surface of cylinder head (2).
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Timing mark (1) on exhaust VVT actuator is aligned with notch (3) of cylinder head.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Crankshaft sprocket key (4) is aligned with notch (3) of cylinder block.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A141065.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "104.587mm" ver = "01" gw = "144" gh = "280"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install timing chain cover and crankshaft pulley. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1406018"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
 Install water pump pulley. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1606015"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install cylinder head cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1406011"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install oil pan. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1506004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install engine assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1406016"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
